com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium.dom

Interface DOMFormControlElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DOMElement, DOMEventTarget, DOMNode, SearchContext
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DOMInputElement, DOMSelectElement, DOMTextAreaElement

    public interface DOMFormControlElement
extends DOMElement
    Represents DOM HTML Form Control such as input, select, textarea, etc.

    • Method Detail

      • isEnabled

        boolean isEnabled()
        Indicates whether form control is enabled or disabled.
        Returns:
        true when form control is enabled.

      • setValue

        void setValue(java.lang.String value)
        Sets value for input element, textarea element and select element. This method is equivalent of setValue(value, false).
        Parameters:
        value - a string that represents a new value in the control.

      • getValue

        java.lang.String getValue()
        Returns value of element. For select element, it returns the value of the selected option if present. If no selected option, an empty string is returned. If element doesn't fall into input element, textarea element and select element categories, an empty string is returned.
        Returns:
        a string that represents value in the form control.

      • getForm

        DOMFormElement getForm()
        Returns the FORM element containing this control. Returns null if this control is not within the context of a form.
